parser.emptyParser: Does not process the log, directly returns the original log line
parser.emptySplitToParts: Does not split the log, treats the entire line as a single part
parser.mergeNearbyParts: Merges adjacent parts, combines specified range of parts into one part
parser.mergeUntilChar: Merges specified range of parts until a specified character is encountered
parser.removeBlankPart: Removes blank strings from the split results
parser.splitByWordSeparator: Splits the log line by whitespace characters, can add sub-operations to further process parts
parser.splitPartWithChar: Splits the log line by whitespace characters, can add sub-operations to further process parts
parser.splitPostProcess: Does not process the log, directly returns the original log line
parser.trimWithChar: Removes specific characters from the beginning and end of the specified part
parser.trimWithIndex: Removes a specified number of characters from the beginning and end

toolTip.loadingTemplateWarning: Whether to discard the current table content and load a template.

toolTip.logForeground: The text color of logs at this level
toolTip.logLevelCombo: Select log level, logs with a level greater than or equal to selected level will be displayed
toolTip.logSample: Log sample, a complete line of log. The content filled in will be used by the log parser, and the log line will be divided into a list of strings, each corresponding to the columns in the column information table
